cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CC

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for predicting lexical entailment. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves feature extraction and iterative procedures, which are common in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of distributional vectors and the analysis of their behavior suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of Hearst patterns, which are a well-known technique for identifying lexical relations, could suggest cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category.
